{{Infobox St. Louis neighborhood <!-- Basic info ----------------> | neighborhood = Grand Center Arts District | neighborhoodnumber = 77 | wards = [[Ward 19, St. Louis City|19]] <!-- images -----------> | image = Fox_theater_stl.jpg | caption = The Fox Theatre is one of the largest theatres in Grand Center. | map = STL Neighborhood Map 77.PNG | mapcaption = Location of Grand Center within [[St. Louis]] <!-- Statistics ---------------------> | area_sq_mi = 0.57 | population = 3,562 | population_as_of = 2010 | population_footnotes = <ref>[http://stlcin.missouri.org/nbr/neighprofile.cfm?neighnum=77 Census Summary By Neighborhoods]</ref> <!-- Area/postal codes & others --------> | zipcodes = Parts of 63106, 63108, 63113 | areacode = 314 | website = [http://stlouis-mo.gov/neighborhoods/profile.cfm?neighborhood=Covenant%20Blu%20Grand%20Center stlouis-mo.gov] }}
The '''Grand Center Arts District''' is located in the '''[[Midtown St. Louis]] ''' '''[[Historic district (United States)|Historic District]] ''' on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] north of the [[Saint Louis University]] campus. Referred to colloquially as Grand Center, the neighborhood was formally known as Covenant Blu-Grand Center.<ref>http://dynamic.stlouis-mo.gov/census/neigh_comp.cfm</ref> The neighborhood is a member of the [[Global Cultural Districts Network]].
Grand Center is the site of numerous arts and entertainment venues including the [[Fox Theatre (St. Louis)|Fox Theatre]], [[Powell Symphony Hall]] (home of the [[St. Louis Symphony Orchestra]]), the [[Contemporary Art Museum Saint Louis]], the [[Pulitzer Arts Foundation]], the [[Sheldon Concert Hall]], [[Clyde C. Miller Career Academy]], and Jazz St. Louis.
The neighborhood is an eclectic mix of restored historic structures and newer buildings with street art and neon signage centered on Strauss Park at the intersection of [[Grand Boulevard (St. Louis)|Grand Boulevard]] and Washington Ave. It includes [[Third Baptist Church (St. Louis, Missouri)|Third Baptist Church]], the St. Louis Black Repertory Theatre Company,<ref>http://www.theblackrep.org</ref> the [[Grand Center Arts Academy]], [[KDHX | KDHX Community Media]], [[KWMU|St. Louis Public Radio (KWMU)]], the [[Kranzberg Arts Foundation|Kranzberg Arts Center]], and the headquarters of the [[KETC |Nine Network of Public Media (KETC)]], a PBS affiliate.<ref name="Bartek">{{cite news|url=https://www.stlbeacon.org/#!/content/27507/grandcenter101212|title=The allure of the arts: New businesses thrive in Grand Center|last=Bartek|first=Elizabeth|date=18 October 2012|work=[[St. Louis Beacon]]|accessdate=10 November 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130720014459/https://www.stlbeacon.org/#!/content/27507/grandcenter101212|archivedate=20 July 2013|df=}}</ref> It is near the [[Grand (St. Louis MetroLink)|Grand MetroLink station]].
